items.description: is a data structure that represents a page of results in a larger dataset. It provides information on the current page being displayed, the total number of pages available, and the total number of elements in the dataset. The class also includes a static method for creating a new PageInfo instance from a Pageable and a Page object.
items.name: PageInfo

items.description: creates a `PageInfo` object containing page-related information, such as the current page number, size, total pages, and total elements, based on provided `Pageable` and `Page` objects.

params.name: pageable
params.description:
pagination state, providing the current page number and page size for generating the page of data.

* `getPageNumber()` represents the current page number.
* `getPageSize()` indicates the number of elements per page.
* `getTotalPages()` displays the total number of pages in the collection.
* `getTotalElements()` shows the overall number of elements in the collection.

params.name: page
params.description:
current page being processed, providing the total number of elements on that page.

* `pageNumber`: The number of the page being returned.
* `pageSize`: The size of the page being returned.
* `totalPages`: The total number of pages in the result set.
* `totalElements`: The total number of elements in the result set.

returns.description:
a `PageInfo` object containing page number, size, total pages, and total elements.

* `pageNumber`: The number of the page being accessed.
* `pageSize`: The size of each page being accessed.
* `totalPages`: The total number of pages in the collection.
* `totalElements`: The total number of elements in the collection.

structured.description: An `AuthenticationController` class that implements the `AuthenticationApi` interface using Spring Webflux. The controller handles login requests and returns a response entity with the user ID and JWT token obtained from the authentication service. The `login()` method takes a valid `LoginRequest` object, calls the `login()` method of the `AuthenticationService`, creates a new response entity with the user ID and JWT token, and returns it. The `createLoginHeaders()` method is used to generate the HTTP headers with the user ID and JWT token.

items.description: Implements an authentication API and handles login requests through its `login()` method. The method takes a valid `LoginRequest` object as input and returns a response entity with the user ID and JWT token in the HTTP headers.
items.name: AuthenticationController

items.description: Processes a `LoginRequest` and returns an `ResponseEntity` with an `ok` status code, headers created by the `createLoginHeaders` method, and built.

params.name: loginRequest
params.description: user authentication request containing the necessary credentials for logging into the application.

returns.description: a response entity with an OK status and custom headers containing authentication data.

items.name: login

items.description: Creates HTTP headers for login purposes, adding a user ID and JWT token obtained from an authentication data object.

params.name: authenticationData
params.description: user's login details, providing the user ID and JWT token for authentication purposes.

returns.description: an HTTP headers object containing the user ID and JWT token of the authenticated user.

items.name: createLoginHeaders

structured.description: A REST controller that implements the AmenitiesApi interface. The controller handles various operations related to amenities, including listing all amenities for a given community, adding a new amenity, deleting an existing amenity, and updating an existing amenity. The controller uses dependencies on Spring Data JPA and Spring Web Flux to perform these operations.

items.description: Is a RESTful API controller that handles requests related to amenities. It provides methods for retrieving all amenities, listing all amenities for a specific community, adding new amenities to a community, deleting an existing amenity, and updating an amenity. The controller uses dependency injection to inject the necessary services (AmenityService and AmenityApiMapper) to perform these operations.
items.name: AmenityController

items.description: Retrieves amenity details from a database using a JPA service and maps them to an `AmenityDetailsResponse` object, returning a `ResponseEntity` with a status code indicating the result of the operation.

params.name: amenityId
params.description: identifying code of an amenity, which is used to retrieve information about that amenity from the database.

items.name: getAmenityDetails

items.description: Retrieves a set of amenities from the database using `JpaService`, and maps them to a set of `GetAmenityDetailsResponse` objects using `Mapper`. It then returns a `ResponseEntity` with the mapped response set.

params.name: communityId
params.description: identifier of the community whose amenities are to be listed.

returns.description: a set of `GetAmenityDetailsResponse` objects containing the details of all amenities for a given community.

items.name: listAllAmenities

items.description: Creates amenities for a given community based on user input and returns an `AddAmenityResponse` object containing the newly created amenities or a `ResponseEntity` indicating that the resource could not be found.

params.name: communityId
params.description: ID of the community to which the amenities will be added.

params.name: request
params.description: AddAmenityRequest object containing the amenities to be added to the community, which is used by the `amenitySDJpaService` to create the new amenities in the database.

returns.description: a `ResponseEntity` object representing a successful addition of amenities to a community.

items.name: addAmenityToCommunity

items.description: Deletes an amenity from the database using the `amenitySDJpaService`. If the amenity is successfully deleted, a `NO_CONTENT` status code is returned; otherwise, a `NOT_FOUND` status code is returned.

params.name: amenityId
params.description: ID of the amenity to be deleted.

returns.description: a `ResponseEntity` object with a status code of either `NO_CONTENT` or `NOT_FOUND`, depending on whether the amenity was successfully deleted or not.

items.name: deleteAmenity

items.description: Updates an amenity's details based on a request body, and returns a response entity indicating whether the update was successful or not.

params.name: amenityId
params.description: ID of the amenity being updated.

params.name: request
params.description:
UpdateAmenityRequest object that contains the details of the amenity to be updated.

* `@Valid`: Indicates that the request body must be validated using the provided bean validation configuration.
* `@RequestBody`: Represents the request body as a whole, which contains the updates for the amenity.

returns.description:
a response entity with a status code of either `NO_CONTENT` or `NOT_FOUND`, depending on whether the amenity was successfully updated.

* `isUpdated`: A boolean value indicating whether the amenity was successfully updated or not.
* `HttpStatus`: The HTTP status code associated with the response, which can be either `NO_CONTENT` (204) or `NOT_FOUND` (404).
